      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's understandable to feel paralyzed when the perceived scale of the problem seems absolute, making any small action feel utterly insignificant. Perhaps shifting the focus from \"saving the whole thing\" to \"caring for what is good *while* it exists\" can offer a different perspective. Meaning can sometimes be found not in achieving a permanent outcome, but in the depth and quality of our experience and connection to others in this limited time. Allow yourself the space to simply witness and be present, even amidst the difficult reality.",
      "source": "target",
